String: String is a Java class
We can create many String objects
We can store a sequence of characters in a String

//1st way of creating String
String name = "John";
String address = "";
String phone = "";


//2nd way of creating a String
String name = new String("John"); // This way requires more memory


//The way we create an object in Java
Random random = new Random(); // Random class object
Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in); // Scanner class object

Date date = new Date(); // Date class object




String methods: They are used for updating, extracting, removing, replacing, comparing, manipulating the data that String object stores.


NOTE: DO NOT EVER USE == for comparing strings and all the other objects
because == compares objects addresses in the memory not the values

primitive == primitive

"abcdab"

"ab" == "ab"

str.substring(0, 2) == str.substring(str.length() - 2) -> false
str.substring(0, 2).equals(str.substring(str.length() - 2)) -> true




